Ideas:

Widget for instant data collectiion!!!

Sensor Kit!




User Flow:
Background:
Hour 1: Sample pressure → Save to DB
Hour 2: Sample pressure → Save to DB
Hour 3: Sample pressure → Save to DB
    ↓
User gets notification "Fill survey!"
    ↓
Query DB: Get all LocalPressureData since last survey
    ↓
Attach to SurveySession
    ↓
Submit survey + all hourly data to server
    ↓
Clear/delete those LocalPressureData samples
    ↓
Start collecting again hourly

RealTimeData:
User taps "Start Survey"
    ↓
Start 1-sec sampling → RealTimeData array
    ↓
User fills form, taps "Submit"
    ↓
Attach RealTimeData + LocalPressureData to SurveySession
    ↓
Submit to server
    ↓
Clear survey data
WidgetSnapshot:
User presses widget
    ↓
Sample for 30 sec
    ↓
Save WidgetSnapshot to DB independently
    ↓
Can be submitted separately or ignored



IRB approval from Northeastern's ethics board
Apple Developer account ($99/yr — now you actually need it)
Research proposal submitted to Apple
Two stages of entitlement:

Development entitlement → for building and testing
Distribution entitlement → for TestFlight/App Store

